      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne Botanic Garden, ¶ 5 February 1868. ¶  ¶ I am sending you again a few newspaper cuttings, esteemed Professor, that might be welcome for your ¶  ¶ Mittheilungen ¶ , ¶ Mittheilungen aus Justus ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">68.02.05a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To August Petermann</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Sammlung Perthes Archiv,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">SPA ARCH<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">PGM<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">328</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Forschungsbibliothek Gotha der Universität Erfurt</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotated by Petermann 'Erh. 1. April 1868' [Received 1 April 1868].<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>For a published version of this letter,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>see Voigt (1996),<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>p. 87.</p>
               </note>Melbourne, im bot. Garten</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">5/2/68</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ich sende Ihnen, verehrter Herr Professor, wieder ein paar Zeitungs-Auszüge, die Ihnen für Ihre "Mittheilungen" willkommen sein möchten, namentlich die kurze Notiz über Capt. Cadells bedeutende Resultate.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Prinz Alfred besuchte meinen Garten, in welchem er zwei junge Tannen (Abies Alberti von Californien u. Saxono-Gothaea conspicua von Patagonien) pflanzte.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In Ihren Mittheilungen habe ich keinen Bericht über die letzte Reise MacIntyre's von Coopers Creek nach dem Flinders Flusse gesehen. Vielleicht ist mir die Nummer nicht zugänglich geworden, da ich das deutsche Vereinslocal während meiner längeren Krankheit nicht besuchen konnte. Ich schnitt aus der Ag. Zeitung die Spalten aus, welche den vollständigen Bericht mit<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">genauen</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>astronomischen Beobachtungen gaben u sandte Ihnen denselben zur Zeit.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>McIntyres Reise ist die einzige, welche in dieser Richtung, wirklich<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">sehr genaue</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>astronomische Data lieferte. Es wäre schade, wenn dieser schöne Beitrag zur Geographie in Zeitungsspalten eines politischen Tagsblattes begraben blieben.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Wiederholt haben Sie mich gütig durch Übersendung von Ihren oder durch Sie erschienenen Aufsätzen erfreut wofür ich herzlich danke. Jüngst habe ich eine Anzahl Baumfarne nach Deutschland gesandt u meinen Agenten gebeten einen derselben an den herzogl. Garten in Gotha zu senden. Würden dort auch Sämereien austral. Gewächse willkommen sein.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Stets der Ihre</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne Botanic Garden,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">5 February 1868.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am sending you again a few newspaper cuttings, esteemed Professor, that might be welcome for your<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Mittheilungen</seg>,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Mittheilungen aus Justus Perthes' geographischer Anstalt</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">, edited by Petermann.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>especially the brief notice on<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Captain Cadell's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>significant results.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">T</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">he telegram sent by<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">F</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">rancis Cadell from Bowen on his</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style=""> </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">return from his sea-borne exploration of n</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">orthern Australia wa</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">s widely reported in the press; see,</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for example,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">, 10 January 1868, p. 5.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Prince Alfred<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Alfred, Duke of Edinburgh.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>visited my Gardens, where he planted two young conifers (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Abies albertii</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>from California<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Saxono-Gothaea</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Saxe-Gothaea</seg>?</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">conspicua</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>from Patagonia).</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have not seen a report on MacIntyre's<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Duncan McIntyre.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="2"/>last journey from Coopers Creek to the Flinders River in your<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Mittheilungen</seg>. Perhaps the number was not accessible to me, as I was unable to visit the German Club's rooms during my longish illness. I<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>cut the paragraphs out of the Ag.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>newspaper and sent them to you; they gave a complete report with<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">exact</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>astronomical observations.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Age</seg>, 23 November 1866, p. 5 and subsequent issues. As M indicates, McIntyre’s<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>journal, as published<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>there, includes a number of astronomically-determined positions. Petermann had<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>already<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>published<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in November 1867<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>an account of McIntyre's journey, based on what the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Age</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>had published<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and almost certainly prepared from the copy of this that M sent him,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>but focusing on specifically geographical matters including the astronomically-determined data; see<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Petermann (1867)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>associated<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>map,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">McIntyre's reise in Central-Australien, 1865 &amp; 1866</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(see National Library of Australia's digitized<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>copy <ref target="https://protect-au.mimecast.com/s/yaLHCE8knvs34X00WcN-th0?domain=nla.gov.au">http://nla.gov.au/nla.obj-232431714</ref>). M to A. Petermann,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>29 February 1868 (in this edition as 68-02-29a) reports the receipt of the paper and map.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>McIntyre's journey is the only one in this direction to provide<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">very precise</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>astronomical data. It would be a pity, if this splendid contribution to geography were to remain buried in the newspaper columns of a political daily paper.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I thank you sincerely, that you have repeatedly given me pleasure by kindly sending me your essays or those published by you. I have recently sent a number of tree<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>ferns to Germany and asked my agent<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>O. W. Sonder. See also M to A. Petermann, October 1867<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 67-10-00), and M to J. Lange, 14 August 1868<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 68-08-14a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to send one of them to the Ducal Gardens in Gotha. Would seeds of Australian plants also be welcome there?</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Always yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Abies albertii</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Saxono-Gothaea conspicua</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
